OL,3,CMan wore all 13 shirts at the 'same
OL,4,Ctime to avoid paying for hold baggage'
OL,6,FHe said: "I didn't want to cause a
OL,7,Ffuss so I paid for it, but I was
OL,8,Ffrustrated. I knew it was a bit heavy
OL,9,Fbut I'd just thrown some clothes in
OL,10,Fthere not thinking about it to be
OL,11,Fhonest.J"It was really galling because
OL,12,Fmy shirts wouldn't have come to #48.
OL,13,FThey are the type you get in the Lidl
OL,14,Fmiddle aisle. I asked if I could bin
OL,15,Fthem all but they said no."JThe night
OL,16,Fbefore Phil returned home from
OL,17,FBenidorm he thought up a plan to don
OL,18,Fevery item of clothing in the bag
OL,19,Fother than a couple of pairs of shoes.
