OL,3,CMan wore all 13 shirts at the 'same
OL,4,Ctime to avoid paying for hold baggage'
OL,6,FIn the bag were 13 shirts, two pairs
OL,7,Fof trousers, four pairs of shorts and
OL,8,Ffive pairs of underpants.
OL,10,FMr Lisle said: "I was getting ready to
OL,11,Fcome back. So I put everything on to
OL,12,Fsee how they fitted. Every shirt,
OL,13,Fevery pair of underpants, every pair
OL,14,Fof shorts and trousers. I was
OL,15,Froasting. If I was an octopus I'd have
OL,16,Fgot the shoes on too."JThe following
OL,17,Fday, after getting through security
OL,18,Fand duty free, Phil went into the
OL,19,Fbathroom and tipped the bag upside
OL,20,Fdown before putting on every item of
OL,21,Fclothing he could manage.
