OL,3,CMan wore all 13 shirts at the 'same
OL,4,Ctime to avoid paying for hold baggage'
OL,6,FHe added: "I started with the small
OL,7,Fshirts, obviously, and then went for
OL,8,Fthe bigger and more loose ones at the
OL,9,Fend.
OL,11,F"I had 13 shirts on, four shorts, two
OL,12,Ftrousers and five underpants. Good
OL,13,Fgrief I could hardly walk, and yet I'm
OL,14,Fnot sure many people realised. I must
OL,15,Fhave been 20 stone.J"Most of my mates
OL,16,Fdidn't seem to be aware. One of them
OL,17,Fasked how many shirts I was wearing
OL,18,Fand I just waved it away. I actually
OL,19,Fthought I was bound to be stopped
OL,20,Fbefore I boarded, but no-one else said
OL,21,Fa thing.
