OL,3,CMan wore all 13 shirts at the 'same
OL,4,Ctime to avoid paying for hold baggage'
OL,6,F"When we got on I told my mate to get
OL,7,Fhis camera out and I started taking
OL,8,Fthe shirts off one by one. Loads of
OL,9,Fpeople were laughing. I took the
OL,10,Fshirts off, and then I took a breather
OL,11,Fand started taking my trousers off."
OL,13,FA video taken by Phil's friend Daniel
OL,14,FCollins showed Mr Lisle taking his
OL,15,Flayers of clothes off while passengers
OL,16,Flaughed after watching him. Phil said
OL,17,Fhe had been a little worried he might
OL,18,Fget in trouble, but even the airline
OL,19,Fstaff saw the funny side.
